  "formula": "1d100",
  "description": "<p>Use this oracle to define the main attributes of a moon. </p><p>A moon is always smaller than the planetary body it orbits, so the moon size results are not equivalent of the planet size results. </p><p>Once you roll for the moon size, cross-reference it with the planetary body size to determine the moon base gravity. Then, roll the density to determine the gravity modifier.</p>",
